Day 4: Yoga with Adriene - Yoga For Your Back. Today is a day for the discovery of the interconnection of your body. While today may focus on the back, this session really engages your whole body. We come to realize that our bodies come together at and are strengthened and supported by our backs and core. There are quite a few stretches in there where you get good engagement in your core, and the stretch seems to extend from the tips of your fingers down through the feet. This really highlights the interconnection of all the parts of our body. The strength of our core flows through our backs and into our limbs. This was quite a enjoyable session and I learned a lot about myself today. Thank you Adriene! Namaste.

OK - Sorry in advance for the novel but I never comment on things yet this is too important to me not to.  You'd really have know me to understand how ground breaking this is for me.  I'll be 47 the end of November and I used to do ballet until my mid teens but no exercise at all since then.  I've been fortunate to have a high metabolism I suppose or something as I've had 4 beautiful children but most would never know.  I've had arthritis in my spine since age 19, mild scoliosis, the usual Degenerative Disc Disease, 2 ruptured discs a couple of bulging discs, and then in 2011 I was in a car accident and fractured two bones in my back at L1/L2.  I didn't listen and went back to work 2 wks later not letting myself heal.  Needless to say, I've suffered chronic back pain for a very long time.  Injections, MRIs, Orthopedic doctors and surgeons, Neurosurgeons, and I was finally told "some people just have to take pain meds every day to get by".  I left that office in tears a year ago.  I had taken strong pain meds for years and I couldn't accept that so I stopped the pain meds in April and had just been living with the pain (not very well mind you as I only leave the house when necessary).  

I've always thought yoga would be a great way to start getting healthy - I stumbled across your Yoga for Beginners and bookmarked it at least 6 months ago - never did it - but I intended to.  Someday.  A week ago, someday finally happened.  I did it and I survived.  I found the 30 day challenge and started with that.  After my third yoga session ever, my back hurt SO bad I couldn't stand it but I *KNEW* that my body was just being forced to move in ways it should have been moving and stretching all along.  After the 4th one (day 3 of the 30 day challenge), it hit me... I wasn't hurting.  At all.  I felt good.  I wanted to leave the house - to take a shower - to do something - and I haven't had this kind of feeling in more years than I can remember.  I know I'm only just starting this (just completed day 4 for the back and it was amazing) but I can see where this is going and I like that direction so much.  I even feel like walking and baby stepping into some cardio.

Adriene - I just have to thank you for providing these videos and being so adorable, easy to follow, encouraging, but not over the top lol!  You are making this so easy for me and I look forward to my sessions.  Even considering doing more than one a day because it feels so good!  I'm getting more flexible and feel like I did back in my teens during all of those ballet and pointe classes.  I never thought I would feel that again.  I've been so worried as 2 of my kids (my 15 and 21 yr old) have been starting to have a lot of back pain.  My son has always been active with basketball in high school but now in college he's not as active and really suffering.  My daughter does all star competitive cheerleading so lots of tumble, stretching and exercise but still starting to really experience pain and I know what that feels like and never want them down the medication road.  I am sharing these with them and can't wait to see how they do.  I know they'll love you as much as I do!  

Anyway, I just felt the need to tell you that you are making an indescribable difference in at least one life.  And hopefully two young lives that can start this practice and use it for a very long time.

THANK YOU,

LeAnn

I knew that wasn't the solution for me, so I started doing a few yoga poses on my own during my moments of most severe pain. I looked up pinterest yoga plans, yoga youtube videos, 30 day fix plans, all sorts of beginner yoga. I started to feel discouraged because I felt even more pain than before. Then I came across this 30 day plan... I am only on day four and I can already take a deep breath without pain! I am amazed at how wonderful I feel already! Compared to any other beginner yoga videos, these have been the most awakening, informal, easy to follow, and all with a bit of humor :) The most amazing thing is that I actually look forward to morning yoga now. I will report back when I finish a full 30 days, but I already know I'm going to feel amazing. I am so glad I found your videos. Also, I'm 28 and have been battling an incurable indolent cancer for 3 years now. I can't even count how many times I have been told that the way I was feeling was something I needed to accept. I am SO glad I didn't listen. Thank you so much!!

Hi Adriene!

First off, let me say how much I love your videos. I've been doing yoga consistently for five months now, which is the longest time I've exercised in a decade. I love it.

I do have one wish though. I wish that you'd join us for savasana. Since it's the most precious posture, and you want us to fully embrace it, it'd be nice if you stayed in savasana with us just for a minute or two. When the music for the end of the video comes on, it feels like I should just get up and be done, but I know I'm missing out on the benefits of savasana when I do that. If I had you doing it as well, I'd be more likely to stay in the posture.

Regardless of that small request, I am so glad I found you. You've helped me learn to love exercise, and really treasure the time I take to do yoga each day. Thank you so much for all you do.
